<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5671] Static compilation of calling increment operator on Integer fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5671</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in short: calling the ++ operator on an Integer does not increment the value when using static compilation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;IntegerIncrementStaticCompilationBug {

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt; index = 0

    @groovy.transform.CompileStatic
    void increment() {
	index++
    }
}

def b = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; IntegerIncrementStaticCompilationBug()
b.increment(); b.increment(); b.increment()

println b.index
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This script should print &quot;3&quot;, but it prints &quot;0&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Works find when CompileStatic annotation is removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
